result.text:
Deputy Secretary to the Treasury (DST), Patrick Ocailap is currently in China for the FOCAC (Forum on China Africa Cooperation Meetings)

 He has visited the Tianjin Light Industry Vocational Training College, Luban Workshop which is one of the Pillars of FOCAC, on skilling and technology transfer to Africa. 

Uganda is one of the countries where the Luban Workshop model has been established. The DST met the Ugandan students currently undergoing a three months training at the center.

He encouraged the students  to grasp the skills and be part of the knowledge economy transformation pillars when they return to the  Luban Workshop centre in Uganda.
